<title>HONG KONG: Wah Nam year net loss HK$48.65 mln.</title>
<headline>Wah Nam year net loss HK$48.65 mln.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended December 31</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	3.45 loss  vs  3.65 loss</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents) nil	  vs  nil</p>
<p>    Exceptional items     10.35 loss vs  17.80 loss</p>
<p>    Net			 48.65 loss vs  45.11 loss</p>
<p>    Turnover		  173.04     vs  126.45</p>
<p>    Company name	    Wah Nam Group Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close	     June 18-25</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	N/A</p>
<p>NOTE - Wah Nam Group is an investment holding company with subsidiaries engaging in the making of consumer electronics and electrical products, plastic and electrical goods and ceramic tiles, property investment and construction and administration of infrastructure projects.</p>
<p>The company changed its financial year-end to December 31 from April 30. Comparative figures are for eight months ended December 31, 1995.</p>
<p>Net is after an exceptional loss on disposal of investment properties and revaluation deficit arising on revaluation of investment properties.</p>
<p>Total dividend for year is nil vs nil (for eight months).</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong newsroom (852) 2843 6368</p>
